Jacoco is the replacement for Emma

To create a jacoco.xml file, use the Maven or Ant support.
From the command line, Jacoco only creates a jacoco.exec file.
But, Codecov needs an xml file.  
To convert jacoco.exec to jacoco.xml:
Change
http://eclemma.org/jacoco/trunk/doc/examples/build/build.xml
(I only need the report target, there is no need to 
specify Java source files, and remove the html and xml output.)


Integration with Code

Manual for command-line use: http://eclemma.org/jacoco/trunk/doc/agent.html

Download the latest snapshot from https://oss.sonatype.org/service/local/artifact/maven/redirect?g=org.jacoco&a=jacoco&e=zip&v=LATEST
which is linked from
http://eclemma.org/jacoco/

cd ~/java 
rm -rf jacoco jacoco-0.7.8
mkdir jacoco-0.7.8
ln -l jacoco-0.7.8 jacoco
cd jacoco-0.7.8
wget -O jacoco-0.7.8.zip http://search.maven.org/remotecontent?filepath=org/jacoco/jacoco/0.7.8/jacoco-0.7.8.zip
unzip jacoco-0.7.8.zip

To run:

* Delete the file
* Run repeatedly the following

-javaagent:${HOME}/java/jacoco/lib/jacocoagent.jar

cd $pl/java
make -C $pl/java test
mv $pl/java/jacoco.exec $pl


===========================================================================

mvn jacoco:prepare-agent test jacoco:report
